               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18420228-1129-charge-1" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-1129-18420228 t18420228-1129-offence-1 t18420228-1129-verdict-1"></join>
               <p>1129. <persName id="def1-1129-18420228" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1129-18420228" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1129-18420228" type="surname" value="HARRIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1129-18420228" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">CHARLES HARRIS</hi>
                  </persName> was <hi rend="italic">again</hi> indicted<rs id="t18420228-1129-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18420228-1129-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18420228-1129-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="embezzlement"></interp> for embezzlement.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CLARKSON</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420228-name-1529" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1529" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1529" type="surname" value="KIRK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1529" type="given" value="THOMAS BELL"></interp>THOMAS BELL KIRK</persName>
                  </hi>. It was the prisoner's duty to take out goods to my customers—my wife prepared the bills for these goods—I scarcely ever made them out—the prisoner bad the bills given him to take out—I never received from him 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., paid on account of Mr. Tindall, on the 5th of Fe<lb></lb>bruary—after the case with respect to the gin, I sent to Mr. Tindal a bill of 12<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 2<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., including the 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., and then found the 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. had been paid.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALLANTINE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Was it his duty to account in the evening? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> It was, it has been sometimes postponed when he had not the means of paying—I think this charge was not stated before the Magistrate—I did not discover it till after he was given into custody—I do not know that there was no charge made against him till he came in this session and surrendered—when I found this bill had been paid, I gave notice to my solicitor, which was last Friday week—I did not hear from his friends that he meant to bring an action against me for false imprisonment—I have not heard that he meant to prosecute me for the</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184202280242"></xptr>
               <p>other charge—the only thing I heard was from his uncle—he said if the lad was innocent he would have justice done him—I think it was on Thursday I found the bill was paid, and on Friday I came to town, and gave instructions to my attorney.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Was it before that that you heard this? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I cannot say.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Will you swear that you did not go and give notice to your at<lb></lb>torney within two hours of this threat to you? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I cannot speak with justice on the subject—I have seen the uncle repeatedly—I saw him one evening last week in my parlour—I cannot say on what day.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420228-name-1530" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1530" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1530" type="surname" value="KIRK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1530" type="given" value="PHILLIPPA"></interp>PHILLIPPA KIRK</persName>
                  </hi>. The prisoner never accounted to me for the receipt of 25. on the 5th of February from Mr. Tindal—I make out the bills ge<lb></lb>nerally, but Mr. Kirk does sometimes—this bill—(<hi rend="italic">looking at one</hi>)—is not my writing, nor my husband's, nor my bar-maid's.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Do you mean that the prisoner had no authority to receive this money? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No, sir—I make out the bills and give them to him to receive—he came to me on the Saturday, the 12th of February, I think it was in the morning, and desired me to make out Mr. Tindalf's account, and it was 12<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 2<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—I remarked that Mr. Tindall's bill had stood unusually long—he said if I would make out the bill on the Monday, he would present it and get the money—I have been talking this matter over with my husband—Mr. Tindall's accounts are kept on a slate—I looked on the slate to see it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420228-name-1531" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1531" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1531" type="surname" value="HUDDY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1531" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>ELIZABETH HUDDY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am barmaid to the prosecutor—the prisoner ne<lb></lb>ver accounted to me for 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. received on 5th of February from Mr. Tindall—this bill is not my writing.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420228-name-1532" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1532" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1532" type="surname" value="MASTERS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420228-name-1532" type="given" value="ELLEN"></interp>ELLEN MASTERS</persName>
                  </hi>. My sister is living with Mr. Tindall, and superintends his family—I was at his house on the 5th of February, the prisoner brought this bill to me, and I paid him 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—I wrote a receipt at the bot<lb></lb>tom of it, and he put his mark to it—(<hi rend="italic">read</hi>)—"King's Arms, Peckham<lb></lb>rye. Mr. Tindall, for beer delivered from 15th of January, 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. Received Charles Harris X his mark. 5th of Februarv, 1842."</p>
               <p>
